## Why This Is Asked

Probes production-grade multi-tenant routing with cost control, latency targets, RBAC, and integration with Azure services (Cosmos DB, AD, Cognitive Search, Durable Functions, API Management). Assesses ability to design end-to-end data flow, observability, and testing strategies.

## Key Concepts

- Per-tenant policy and quota management in Cosmos DB
- Multi-model routing: cost-aware model choice + RAG grounding
- Latency budgets and backpressure via Durable Functions
- RBAC via Azure AD and API Management gating
- Grounding via Cognitive Search KB

## Code Example

```javascript
// Minimal routing decision
function chooseEngine(policies, tenantId, workload) {
  const p = policies[tenantId];
  if (!p) return 'GPT-3.5-turbo';
  if (workload.latencyMs > p.latencyBudget) return p.defaultModel;
  if (workload.costPerRequest > p.costBudget) return 'GPT-3.5-turbo';
  return p.preferredModel;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you model tenant quotas in Cosmos DB for fairness during bursts?
- What tests validate SLA adherence under canary deployments?
- How would you implement backpressure across regional deployments and API gateways?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to architect a multi-tenant Azure OpenAI flow integrated with DevOps, covering data lineage, security, and performance.

## Key Concepts
- Azure OpenAI + API Management
- Cognitive Search KB in Blob
- Per-tenant RBAC (Azure AD)
- PII redaction (Text Analytics)
- Data Lake logging
- Canary deployments and end-to-end latency goals

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo orchestration snippet showing tenant context, diff->prompt, and moderation
async function reviewPR(prDiff, tenantId){
  const kb = await loadKB(tenantId);
  const prompt = buildPrompt(prDiff, kb, tenantId);
  const review = await openAiReview(prompt);
  if(hasPIIRisk(review)){ redact(review); }
  await storeLogs(tenantId, {prDiff, review});
  return review.comments;
}
``` 

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate and monitor prompt drift across tenants without leaking data?
- What latency and cost controls would you put in place for high-velocity repos?

