## Code Example
```javascript
// Redaction example
function redactPII(text) {
  return text.replace(/\b\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}\b/g, "[REDACTED_DATE]");
}
```
```javascript
// Budget guard example
function withinBudget(nextTokens, budget, spent) {
  return spent + nextTokens < budget;
}
```

Why This Is Asked

Assess the ability to design a compliant, multi-tenant AI service on Azure with strong data isolation, governance, and cost controls.


## Key Concepts

- Tenant isolation across storage, prompts, and model deployments
- Data governance and lineage with Purview
- PII handling and privacy-by-design in prompts
- Cost controls and API Management gating


## Code Example

```javascript
// Tenant routing sketch
function routeForTenant(req) {
  const tenant = req.headers['X-Tenant'];
  if (!tenant) throw new Error('Missing tenant');
  return {
    deployment: `openai-${tenant}`,
    container: `cosmos-${tenant}`
  };
}
```


## Follow-up Questions

- How would you test for cross-tenant data leakage?
- How would you implement per-tenant budgets and fail-closed behavior?

## Why This Is Asked
Assesses ability to design a secure, scalable OpenAI deployment with strict per-tenant isolation, governance, and rollout strategies in Azure.

## Key Concepts
- Multi-tenant RBAC and per-tenant KBs in Cognitive Search
- Prompt-guard layer to prevent injection and data leakage
- PII redaction with Text Analytics
- Canary rollouts behind API Management
- Auditable logs to Data Lake and RBAC alignment via Azure AD

## Code Example
```javascript
// Guard layer sketch
async function guardPrompt(input, tenantId) {
  const policy = await kb.fetchTenantPolicy(tenantId);
  if (policy.blockList.some(r => input.includes(r))) {
    throw new Error('Input blocked by policy');
  }
  // optional rewriting rules
  return input;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would policy KB updates be rolled out without affecting active tenants?
- What are latency trade-offs and how would you mitigate them at scale?

## Why This Is Asked
This tests real-world infra decisions around data residency, confidential inference, and auditable prompts in a regulated fintech context.

## Key Concepts
- Azure OpenAI in Confidential Computing
- Multi-tenant isolation (RBAC, per-tenant caches)
- Data residency controls and API Management routing
- PII masking and prompt/log redaction
- Audit trails to Data Lake and cost governance

## Code Example
```javascript
// Example: redact and route to OpenAI within tenant boundaries
function preparePrompt(input, tenantId){
  const redacted = redactPII(input);
  const region = getTenantRegion(tenantId);
  if(region !== 'allowed-region') throw new Error('Region violation');
  return callOpenAI(redacted, {tenantId});
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate end-to-end latency under peak load?
- What tests would verify region-boundary enforcement and audit completeness?
